file=Brand Studio/muse/marketplace/generate-creative-ideas/SKILL.md · h=name: generate-creative-ideas\ntype: marketplace\nstatus: copied verbatim (SKILL.md; source's 7 reference files remain in the source repo — see pending note)\nsource: https://skillsmp.com/creators/kapishdima/soundcn/agents-skills-generate-creative-ideas\nsource_repo: https://github.com/kapishdima/soundcn/tree/main/.agents/skills/generate-creative-ideas\nauthor: kapishdima\ncopied_verbatim: true\nfulfills_catalog_entry: ideation-methods (VYON_Skills_Catalog_Full_v2.html, muse/Brand Studio)\nassigned_agent: muse (Brand Studio / Ideation)\nportable: true — pure methodology, no company specifics\npending: the source ships 7 reference files (techniques, methodology, random-words, evaluation, content-ideation, idea-pipeline, prompt-templates) not copied here — named explicitly rather than silently omitted; retrievable from the source repo when depth is needed. The SKILL.md is self-contained for normal operation.\ndate_added: 2026-07-07 · ym(:yvon-compile metadata (auto-derived from skill content 2026-07-20 — review welcome; body verbatim)=tier: 2\ndescription: "**Context questions (step…"\ntriggers: [generate creative ideas]\n\n<!--\nUnmodified copy of "generate-creative-ideas" (kapishdima/soundcn, 684★), fulfilling the\ncatalog's ideation-methods slot (SCAMPER, lateral thinking, constraint-based — this adds a\nfull situation→technique matrix, divergent/convergent split with never-judge-while-generating\ndiscipline, NAF/ICE/Impact-Effort evaluation, a Content Creator Mode with pillars +\nrepurposing chain, and research-grounded AI-creativity guards including the Divergence Guard\nagainst LLM homogenization — directly relevant to this system).\nNOTES FOR THIS SYSTEM:\n1. Muse runs this for GENERATION; the closing phase is always concept-library (dedupe →\nscore → top 3 to spark → register everything). The two are one pipeline.\n2. The Content Creator Mode's pillars/repurposing chain is pulse's main consumption path.\n3. Related-skills pointers (/triz, /deep-research etc.) are source-repo references, not\nlocal skills. RICE mention → vista's skill at venture altitude; here it's per the\nsource's own evaluation table.\n4. The one Thai-language note in the workflow is source flavor — output language follows\nthe operator's, per system convention.\n-->\n · wf:=```\n1. Ask       → "What problem/challenge?"\n2. Context   → Understand current state BEFORE suggesting\n3. Diagnose  → Match situation to technique(s)\n4. Generate  → Walk through technique step-by-step\n5. Evaluate  → Score and filter ideas\n6. Develop   → Shape top ideas into actionable concepts\n7. Output    → Structured ideas + next actions (Thai if user uses Thai)\n```\n\n**Context questions (step 2):**\n\n- "What do you currently do?"\n- "What have you tried?"\n- "What's working? What's not?"\n\n> Anti-pattern: Jumping to solutions without understanding context = generic noise\n · tb=\| Situation                             \| Techniques                                                      \| Combination Recipe                                      \| · tb=\| ------------------------------------- \| --------------------------------------------------------------- \| ------------------------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| Stuck / No ideas                      \| Random Word, Forced Connections, Oblique Strategies             \| Random Word -> Forced Connections -> Dot Vote           \| · tb=\| Need breakthrough                     \| First Principles, Challenging Assumptions, Combinatorial Engine \| HMW -> Worst Idea -> SCAMPER -> Brainwriting            \| · tb=\| Improve existing                      \| SCAMPER, Reverse Brainstorming, TRIZ-AI                         \| SCAMPER -> Reverse Brainstorm -> Impact/Effort          \| · tb=\| Explore systematically                \| Morphological Box, Six Thinking Hats, Constraint Injection      \| Morphological Box -> Constraint Injection -> Clustering \| · tb=\| Reframe problem                       \| How Might We (HMW), Jobs to be Done                             \| HMW -> JTBD -> First Principles                         \| · tb=\| Team ideation                         \| 6-3-5 Brainwriting, Multi-Persona Parallel                      \| Mind Map -> Brainwriting -> Affinity -> Multi-Vote      \| · tb=\| Too many ideas                        \| Impact/Effort Matrix, Idea Clustering, NAF Scoring              \| Clustering -> NAF Quick Score -> Impact/Effort          \| · tb=\| AI ideas too similar                  \| Divergence Guard, Constraint Injection, Incubation Cycling      \| Divergence Guard -> Domain Shift -> Incubation          \| · tb=\| Technical/engineering                 \| TRIZ-AI, First Principles                                       \| TRIZ -> First Principles -> Assumption Mapping          \| · tb=\| Cross-domain innovation               \| Combinatorial Engine, Analogical Thinking                       \| Combinatorial Engine -> Analogical -> Constraint        \| · tb=\| **Content ideas** (blog/video/course) \| Content Pillars, Audience Pain Points, Gap Analysis             \| Pillars -> Pain Points -> SCAMPER -> Validate           \| · tb=\| **Business/product ideas**            \| JTBD, Opportunity Canvas, Lean Validation                       \| JTBD -> HMW -> Morphological -> ICE Score               \| · tb=\| Technique              \| One-liner                                                                          \| · tb=\| ---------------------- \| ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| **SCAMPER**            \| 7 lenses: Substitute, Combine, Adapt, Modify, Put to other use, Eliminate, Reverse \| · tb=\| **Random Word**        \| Random noun -> list attributes -> force connections to problem                     \| · tb=\| **Reverse Brainstorm** \| "How to make it worse?" -> Invert each idea                                        \| · tb=\| **First Principles**   \| Strip to fundamentals -> Rebuild from scratch                                      \| · tb=\| **Six Hats**           \| 6 perspectives: Facts, Feelings, Risks, Benefits, Ideas, Process                   \| · tb=\| **HMW**                \| Reframe as "How Might We [verb] for [user] so that [outcome]?"                     \| · tb=\| **Morphological Box**  \| Parameters x Variations matrix -> Combine systematically                           \| · tb=\| **Analogies**          \| "How does [other domain] solve this?"                                              \| · tb=\| **Assumptions**        \| List assumptions -> Challenge/invert each                                          \| · tb=\| **Forced Connections** \| Combine 2 unrelated concepts                                                       \| · tb=\| **Jobs to be Done**    \| "When [situation], I want [motivation], so I can [outcome]"                        \| · tb=\| **Oblique Strategies** \| Random creative prompts to break deadlocks                                         \| · tb=\| Technique                  \| One-liner                                                              \| · tb=\| -------------------------- \| ---------------------------------------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| **Incubation Cycling**     \| Generate -> Pause -> Fresh restart (no prior context) -> Compare       \| · tb=\| **Combinatorial Engine**   \| Abstract -> Retrieve 3 domains -> Generalize -> Combine -> Instantiate \| · tb=\| **Multi-Persona Parallel** \| Run 4+ personas SIMULTANEOUSLY (not sequentially)                      \| · tb=\| **Constraint Injection**   \| Add random constraint -> Force novel solutions                         \| · tb=\| **Divergence Guard**       \| Force opposite -> Domain shift -> Absurdity injection                  \| · tb=\| **TRIZ-AI**                \| Apply inventive principles (segmentation, nesting, dynamization, etc.) \| · tb=\| **Tree of Thoughts**       \| Explore multiple reasoning branches simultaneously (74% vs CoT 49%)    \| · tb=\| Technique                \| One-liner                                                        \| · tb=\| ------------------------ \| ---------------------------------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| **NAF Quick Score**      \| Rate Novelty + Attractiveness + Feasibility (1-10 each)          \| · tb=\| **Impact/Effort Matrix** \| 2x2: Quick Wins, Big Bets, Fill-ins, Avoid                       \| · tb=\| **ICE Scoring**          \| Impact x Confidence x Ease (1-10 each)                           \| · tb=\| **Idea Clustering**      \| Group similar -> Name clusters -> Pick best from each            \| · tb=\| **Dot Voting**           \| Each person gets 3-5 votes -> Surface favorites                  \| · tb=\| **Assumption Mapping**   \| Map assumptions on Importance x Certainty -> Test riskiest first \| · ie:Idea Evaluation=After generating ideas, ALWAYS offer evaluation. Default to **NAF Quick Score**.\n · tb=\| Criterion          \| Question                            \| Scale \| · tb=\| ------------------ \| ----------------------------------- \| ----- \| · tb=\| **Novelty**        \| How new/surprising is this?         \| 1-10  \| · tb=\| **Attractiveness** \| How well does it solve the problem? \| 1-10  \| · tb=\| **Feasibility**    \| How realistic to implement?         \| 1-10  \| · ### NAF Quick Score (Default)=**Interpretation:**\n\n- Total 24-30: Strong candidate -> develop further\n- Total 18-23: Promising -> refine or combine\n- Total < 18: Weak -> park or discard\n- Feasibility 8+: Worth trying (remaining 20% is implementation)\n- High N+A but low F: Reframe feasibility barriers as new problems to solve\n · tb=\| Situation                     \| Method                  \| · tb=\| ----------------------------- \| ----------------------- \| · tb=\| Quick screening (5+ ideas)    \| NAF or Dot Voting       \| · tb=\| Growth experiments            \| ICE Scoring             \| · tb=\| Data-driven product decisions \| RICE Scoring            \| · tb=\| Complex multi-criteria        \| Weighted Scoring Matrix \| · tb=\| Visual team alignment         \| Impact/Effort 2x2       \| · ### When to Use Which Evaluation=**Rules:**\n\n1. NEVER evaluate during divergent phase -- generate first, judge later\n2. Take a break between generating and evaluating (different mindset)\n3. Different idea types need different criteria (incremental vs disruptive)\n\nDetails: evaluation.md (source repo references/)\n\n · ccm:Content Creator Mode=When ideating for blog posts, videos, courses, or social media:\n · ### Step 1: Define Content Pillars (3-5 themes)=```\nPillar = Core theme that reflects expertise + audience needs\nExample: Excel -> [Formulas, Data Viz, Automation, Tips & Tricks, Career]\n```\n · tb=\| Source      \| Questions                               \| · tb=\| ----------- \| --------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| Pain Points \| What frustrates them most?              \| · tb=\| Questions   \| What do they repeatedly ask?            \| · tb=\| Gaps        \| What's poorly explained by competitors? \| · tb=\| Wishes      \| What do they wish existed?              \| · tb=\| Mistakes    \| What common errors do they make?        \| · ### Step 3: Generate Ideas (use any technique from matrix)=Apply creativity techniques TO the content pillars:\n\n- SCAMPER on existing popular content\n- Reverse brainstorm: "How to make the worst tutorial?"\n- Analogies: "How would Netflix teach Excel?"\n · ### Step 4: Validate Before Creating=```\n[ ] Search demand? (keyword research)\n[ ] Real audience pain point? (comments, surveys)\n[ ] Can I add unique value? (gap analysis)\n[ ] Fits my pillars? (strategy alignment)\n[ ] Would I click this? (title/thumbnail test)\n[ ] Can be repurposed? (1 piece -> 5+ formats)\n```\n · ### Repurposing Chain=```\nBlog post -> YouTube video -> Shorts/Reels -> Social posts -> Email -> Course module\n```\n\nDetails: content-ideation.md (source repo references/)\n\n · idp:Idea Development Pipeline=Shape raw ideas into actionable concepts:\n\n```\n[Generate] -> [Cluster] -> [Evaluate] -> [Develop] -> [Validate] -> [Execute]\n```\n · ### Quick Concept Card (for top ideas)=```\nIDEA: [Name]\nTAGLINE: [One compelling sentence]\nPROBLEM: [What pain it solves]\nSOLUTION: [How it works - 2-3 sentences]\nTARGET USER: [Who benefits]\nKEY INSIGHT: [The "aha" behind this]\nEFFORT: [S / M / L]\nBIGGEST RISK: [What could go wrong]\nQUICKEST TEST: [How to validate cheaply]\nNEXT STEP: [One concrete action]\n```\n · ### Assumption Mapping (for important ideas)=1. List assumptions: "What must be true for this to work?"\n2. Categorize: Desirability / Feasibility / Viability\n3. Map on 2x2: Importance (high/low) x Certainty (high/low)\n4. Test high-importance + low-certainty FIRST\n\nDetails: idea-pipeline.md (source repo references/)\n\n · of:s=Use these when presenting ideas to the user:\n · ### Quick List (5+ ideas)=```\n1. **[Idea Name]** -- [One-line description]\n2. **[Idea Name]** -- [One-line description]\n...\n```\n · ### Scored List (after evaluation)=``` · tb=\| # \| Idea \| N \| A \| F \| Total \| · tb=\|---\|------\|---\|---\|---\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| ...  \| 8 \| 9 \| 7 \| 24    \| · ### Scored List (after evaluation)=```\n · ### Concept Cards (top 3 ideas)=Use the Quick Concept Card format above for each top idea.\n · ### Comparison Matrix (deciding between options)=``` · tb=\| Criteria     \| Idea A \| Idea B \| Idea C \| · tb=\|-------------\|--------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| Novelty     \| 4/5    \| 3/5    \| 5/5    \| · tb=\| Feasibility \| 3/5    \| 5/5    \| 2/5    \| · tb=\| Impact      \| 5/5    \| 3/5    \| 4/5    \| · ### Comparison Matrix (deciding between options)=```\n\n · tb=\| Finding                                                 \| Implication                             \| · tb=\| ------------------------------------------------------- \| --------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| Ask AI HOW to think, not WHAT to think                  \| Process prompts > product prompts       \| · tb=\| Human-first ideation preserves diversity                \| User brainstorms first, THEN AI expands \| · tb=\| LLMs match average creativity (52nd percentile)         \| AI is a partner, not a replacement      \| · tb=\| Homogenization effect (g ~ -0.86)                       \| Use Divergence Guard actively           \| · tb=\| "Creative Scar" -- creativity drops after AI withdrawal \| Don't outsource all creative thinking   \| · tb=\| Tree of Thoughts: 74% vs CoT 49%                        \| Use ToT for complex creative tasks      \| · tb=\| Multi-LLM collaboration enhances originality            \| Stack techniques, vary approaches       \| · tb=\| Only 0.28% of LLM ideas reach top 10% human creativity  \| Push past first outputs aggressively    \| · ### AI Role Rules=- **Best as:** Exploration partner, constraint enforcer, analogy finder, elaborator\n- **Avoid:** Sole ideation source, final decision maker\n- **Timing:** After initial human ideation, not before\n- **Override rate:** Maintain 15-25% human override for optimal outcomes\n · tb=\| Don't                  \| Do Instead                                              \| · tb=\| ---------------------- \| ------------------------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| "Give me ideas for X"  \| "Give me 10 ideas for X that would surprise an expert"  \| · tb=\| Accept first outputs   \| Push past 2-3 rounds; first ideas are "greatest hits"   \| · tb=\| Use AI before thinking \| Brainstorm independently first, then expand with AI     \| · tb=\| "Be creative"          \| Use specific technique (SCAMPER, constraints, personas) \| · ### Anti-Patterns=Details: methodology.md \| prompt-templates.md (source repo references/)\n\n · r:References=- **Step-by-step guides**: techniques.md (source repo references/)\n- **AI methodology & research**: methodology.md (source repo references/)\n- **Random word bank**: random-words.md (source repo references/)\n- **Evaluation frameworks**: evaluation.md (source repo references/)\n- **Content creator ideation**: content-ideation.md (source repo references/)\n- **Idea development pipeline**: idea-pipeline.md (source repo references/)\n- **AI prompt templates**: prompt-templates.md (source repo references/)\n\n · rs:Related Skills=- `/triz` — Systematic innovation methodology (complements brainstorming)\n- `/deep-research` — Research inspiration and cross-industry solutions\n- `/boost-intel` — Critical evaluation of generated ideas\n- `/design-business-model` — Apply creative ideas to business models\n- `/problem-solving` — Structure the problem before ideating\n